review: Dr. Tejswini  kamble 's  friendlyness makes patients even wont feel odd to share the actual health issues  she understands the whole issues and health problems  and give the best conclusion  or choice of treatments . Me and my wife has consulted  her for pregnancy related issues  occurred  after hormonal imbalance  we were panicked as issue was serious and blood reports were completly out of the range and abnormal .. she explained and gave the proper line of treatment which showed the results within couple of weeks and hormone levels became close to normal range.. my wife has decided foe any future  gynecolohical issues she will only visit Dr. Tejaswini  we also suggest others to visit her as she always gives best and easy with *********** ********* solution to person's health issue - Mrs. priyanka krupesh chotaliya.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: I had irregular and heavy periods for three years and went to two doctors one said I have POC's and I need to get operated and other couldn't trace POC's and prescribed medicines which didn't helped my situation instead was heavy on my pocket and worsened my condition month on month.  I visited Dr Tejaswi on a family doctors suggestion, she was extremely friendly she asked to change my diet and lifestyle and prescribed medicines for three months and it really worked wonders. also the most amazing thing is as I wanted to conceive she was very open in suggesting the ways that will have more chances of me getting pregnant. Exactly after three months I got pregnant and I have been going to her for regular visits but unlike others she doesnâ€™t insist on coming to hospital for everything, she asked me to send my medical reports over Whatsapp and would reply everything as normal. She is affordable and is available over phone whenever I needed her suggestions. Once while my first trimester I had blood clots and she suggested to take Hormonal injections by weekly and prescribed medicines which will keep my progesterone levels balanced which helped me to complete my trimester safely. She gave a lot of info on what to eat what to avoid and how travelling by bus, bikes and auto will be harmful to fetus at early stages. As I live in with my husband alone without parents around her suggestions helped me a lot. I am extremely happy to have her as my doctor during my pregnancy.

review:
I myself francisca went to dr.tejeswi kamble for my first pregnancy with reference to one of my family doctor from the day one i had great experience with her as she gave me proper advice related to my food and medicine like how to take and when and most importantly her appointment fees was also less and whenever I use to whats app and ask my doubts she immediately replies. And I didn't knew the pain of c section done by her within 4days i was normal  i would recommend dr. Tejeswi to my friends and relatives too.
Thanks

review: i sushma kamlesh jaiswar i went to dr tejaswi kamble for lower abdomen crampy pain.....doc adviced me to do sonography obs. as my upt was positive....till the time i went for doing usg obs.....doc was about to go but due to my increasing problems she again came back in opd and had a look after me with my sonography reports. she explained me each and everything about issues related to my pregnancy like a friend.
